article.headline: Holy Cross 60, Colgate 58
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Devin Brown scored 13 points and Andrew Beinert added 12 points and four rebounds as Holy Cross edged Colgate 60-58 in Patriot League play Wednesday. With the win, the Crusaders (15-13, 10-3) will be no worse than second seed in the Patriot League Tournament. Ben Jonson led Colgate (9-18, 5-8) with 18 points and six rebounds, and Yaw Gyawu added 14 points. The score was tied at 11-11 after the first seven minutes, but the Crusaders went on a 15-4 run over the next seven minutes to take an 11-point advantage, 26-15. The Raiders scored the next eight points and then tied the score at 28-28 at the half. Colgate started the second half with a 12-3 run to go up 40-31 before Holy Cross responded with a 17-5 spurt and took the lead for good. Both teams end their regular seasons Saturday: Colgate at Navy, Holy Cross at home against Lehigh.
